Products.Name: Luv-a-duck Fresh Duck Breast Fillets
Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Luv-a-duck Fresh Duck Breast Fillets' has a supply limit of 36. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.RichDescription:
Luv-a-Duck Fresh Duck Breast Fillets are tender, meaty and ready to be cooked the way you like. Simply pan fry, then oven finish for crispy skin and juicy pink meat.

Cooking instructions:
Preheat oven to 190 degrees C. Pat duck skin dry, score the skin and season with salt. In a moderate pan, place duck breasts skin side down into the pan for 5 minutes or until skin is golden. Turn duck breast over and cook for a further 2 minutes. Remove from the pan and place on a roasting tray. Roast the duck in the oven for 8-10 minutes to your liking (for best results duck should be cooked medium). Remove from the oven and rest for 5 minutes before slicing.

Storage recommendation: 
Keep refrigerated. Store between 0-4 degrees C. After opening, keep refrigerated and consume within 2 days.

Products.FullDescription: Three Aussie Farmers Lightly Seasoned Pork Schnitzel
Products.RichDescription:
Three Aussie Farmers Lightly Seasoned Pork Schnitzel

There isn’t much that’s beats a schnitty with chips and gravy.  This schnitzel is made with a tender slice of Australian pork, and coated in fresh seasoned breadcrumbs.  It’s quick to cook and not a bad choice when you’re flat out like a lizard drinking.

Cooking Instructions

For crunchiest results dep fry at 190°C for 2 mins.

Alternatively, pan fry as per below:

  1. Heat frypan to med-high heat and cover base with 1-2cm oil.
  2. Heat oil until very hot*.
  3. Add Pork Schnitzels in a single layer and cook for 2 mins.
  4. Turn and cook for a further 2 mins.

*TIP: Test heat by dropping in a breadcrumb – the crumb should sizzle immediately.  Don’t crowd the pan, these schnitzels need room to sizzle!

Or try oven baking

  1. Preheat oven to 180°C (fan forced and conventional).
  2. Bake on a lightly oiled tray for 10 mi, turn then bake for a further 10 mins or until crunchy.
 
Cook times are a guide only and may vary depending on your appliance.

Products.RichDescription: Our premium saltwater Barramundi is nurtured on our family farm, halfway between Darwin and Kakadu National Park. Sustainable farming techniques run deep to the core of Humpty Doo Barramundi's operations. From sustainably-sourced feed to recirculating our water through a purpose-built wetland, our high quality premium saltwater grown Barramundi is produced while protecting our unique surrounding environment. Humpty Doo Barramundi is a superb eating quality Barramundi with a delicate flavour and clean, firm fillet which remains moist when cooked. Ideal for crisp-skin cooking. Humpty Doo Barramundi is a good source of omega 3 fatty acids, phosphorus (for energy) and selenium (for a healthy immune system), making it the perfect choice for you and your family.
